column5: How does the fishing in Sept. compare to the rest of the year? Still good numbers of catches? <{{}}><

Would like info on locations to fish in late september in NW corner of lac seul. I am familiar with spring/summer locations (Broad, sunlight, Mckenzie ), but interested in some spots to try in late sept. Thanks in advance.

Would like info on locations to fish in late september in NW corner of lac seul. I am familiar with spring/summer locations (Broad, sunlight, Mckenzie ), but interested in some spots to try in late sept. Thanks in advance.
Fish below the dam on the English River. There is a boatdock on the river in Ear Falls.
Fish below the dam on the English River. There is a boatdock on the river in Ear Falls.

I thought they asked about lacseul. If so then fishing is very close to the dam. Under the old railrod bridge. If staying at a resort the owner will put you on the spots. Very close fishing at that time of year as they travel back to there spawing areas.

Where is the road that takes you below the dam?
Where is the road that takes you below the dam?

Take your first left after you cross the dam going north. That will take you to Little Canada Camp and you may be able to put a boat in there or rent a boat from the camp. The city dock for Ear Falls is marked with a sign if you proceed North on the highway through Ear Falls. The turn is to the west and you go a mile or so before you reach the dock.
